1. Project Goal
The goal of this project is to build a modern, high-performance, and fully responsive full-stack web application from scratch. The application must feature a professional UI/UX, robust routing, and scalable architecture.

2. Tech Stack & Architecture
Frontend Framework: Next.js (App Router), React, TypeScript

Styling: Tailwind CSS

UI Components: shadcn/ui and Lucide Icons (Focus on modern, clean, glassmorphism or minimalist aesthetic)

Backend/Database: Node.js API routes (Next.js) with mock data initially. Prepare architecture for easy Supabase/Firebase integration later.

Package Manager: pnpm or npm

3. Strict Development Rules
Anti-Lazy Rule: You are an expert senior engineer. You DO NOT use placeholders like //... existing code.... You output the FULL content of the file every time. You do not be lazy.

Clean Code: Keep components modular and strictly typed using TypeScript interfaces. Avoid dumping all logic into a single file.

Security: Never hardcode API keys or secrets. Always use .env.local for environment variables.

Language: Code, variables, and comments must be in English. The actual user interface (UI texts) visible to the end-user should be in Turkish.

